nd political economy.David Kennedy and Martti Koskenniemi have often inspired each other and are both considered “critical” voices in international law, but they have never explored their similarities and differences as deeply as they do here. Of Law and the World takes the form of a conversation, as the authors reflect on the study of international law, the motivations underlying their research, and the payoffs and limitations of their investigations into law’s role in global affairs. They revisit and renew debates about the past and future of the many legalities that shape our world.Erudite, open-minded, and informed by decades of experience and observation, Of Law and the World is an unflinchingly honest confrontation with humanity’s struggle to live together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical legal studies. 0aInternational lawxEconomic aspects. 0aInternational lawxHistory. 0aInternational law-History. 0aInternational law. 0aPower (Social sciences). 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh  acapitalism.  acolonialism.  ademocracy.  adiplomacy.  aempire.  afunctional differentiation.  aidentity.  aimperialism.  alegitimation.  amarx.  aproperty.  apublic private.  arevolutions.  aslavery.  asocial theory.  asovereignty.  atechnocracy.1 aKoskenniemi, Martti, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074970040uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674294899?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674294899423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674294899/original  a978-3-11-074970-0  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles